                    .
                    <lb n="14"/>
                    <space dim="vertical" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
                </ab>
            </div>

            <div type="translation" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
                <head>Translation</head>
                <ab part="N">The Homeland, With Good Fortune, <supplied reason="subaudible">set up the
                    statue of
                </supplied> T<expan>itus</expan> Opp<expan>ius</expan> Aelianus Asclepiodotus, the most splendid
                    consular, governor of Caria and Phrygia, proconsul and corrector of
                    Asia, founder and saviour also of his own homeland; Tib
                    <expan>erius</expan>
                    Cl<expan>audius</expan> Marcianus the first archon <supplied reason="subaudible">set this up/was in
                        charge</supplied>.
                </ab>
            </div>

            <div type="commentary" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
                <head>Commentary</head>
                <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="II.4" evaluate="all" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO"
                                           from="ROOT">II.4</xref>.
                </p>
                <p>For T<expan>itus</expan> Opp<expan>ius</expan> Aelianus Asclepiodotus see fasti, Governors, <xref
                        type="governors" n="OppiusAsclepiodotus" evaluate="all" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" from="ROOT">
                    Oppius Asclepiodotus</xref>.
                </p>
                <p>For Marcianus see fasti: Local Officials, <xref type="local-officials" n="Marcianus" evaluate="all"
                                                                   targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" from="ROOT">Marcianus</xref>.
                </p>
            </div>

